(40, 7, 16, 59, 3, 12, 12, 'by their fruits', 'Fruitfulness and Consistency', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that a tree''s produce reflects its true nature. Matthew discusses knowing individuals by their fruits, while James illustrates that different types of trees cannot bear conflicting fruits.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
