(40, 7, 17, 42, 13, 6, 9, 'bringeth forth good fruit', 'Fruitfulness and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of bearing fruit as a sign of goodness. Matthew highlights that a good tree produces good fruit, while Luke illustrates a fig tree that fails to bear fruit, leading to a call for judgment.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 18, 48, 5, 17, 17, 'bring forth good fruit', 'Fruit and Spiritual Conflict', 'Both passages emphasize the dichotomy between good and evil. Matthew highlights that a good tree cannot produce evil fruit, while Galatians describes the conflict between the flesh and the Spirit, suggesting that one''s nature determines one''s actions.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
