(40, 7, 19, 58, 6, 8, 8, 'bringeth not forth good fruit', 'Judgment of Unfruitful Plants', 'Both passages emphasize the fate of unproductive plants, highlighting that those which do not bear good fruit are destined for destruction. This connection illustrates a common theme of judgment against unfruitfulness.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
